tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE sales_funnel_ab_test_results (
    test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name VARCHAR(255),
    test_element VARCHAR(255),
    test_group VARCHAR(50),
    test_variation VARCHAR(50),
    test_result DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE ab_tests (
    test_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name STRING,
    test_description STRING,
    test_start_date TIMESTAMP,
    test_end_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id UUID REFERENCES ab_tests(test_id),
    user_id UUID,
    variation_name STRING,
    conversion_status BOOLEAN,
    conversion_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id INT NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    variation_id INT,
    conversion BOOLEAN,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SalesFunnelTests (
    test_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name VARCHAR(255),
    test_description TEXT,
    test_start_date TIMESTAMP,
    test_end_date TIMESTAMP,
    test_status BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE TestParticipants (
    participant_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id UUID REFERENCES SalesFunnelTests(test_id),
    participant_name VARCHAR(255),
    participant_email VARCHAR(255),
    participant_group VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE TestResults (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    participant_id UUID REFERENCES TestParticipants(participant_id),
    test_id UUID REFERENCES SalesFunnelTests(test_id),
    result_date TIMESTAMP,
    result_metric_name VARCHAR(50),
    result_metric_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    test_group INT,
    conversion_status VARCHAR(50),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
